result.name: Kashmir Curry House

reviews.text:
Simple and flavorful food.   I tried the veg biryani with a sweet lassi  on an empty stomach and was very satisfied with the food and service.

Updated May 12,2019: 

Decided to take a walk around Sham Shui Po And was able to plan on another return to the Kashmir Curry House.   My companion and I got a broad selection of the menu and were very happy with the food that arrived.  

Nice mix of locals from many cultural backgrounds.   Good prices and better quality.
i used to eat here a lot while living in hk, i LOVE the food! would definitely recommend

Small Indian shop in the heart of Sham Shui Po, I was quickly attracted by their menu since it includes Murtabaks and Parathas (I LOVE THOSE). 

To be honest, I wasn’t expecting a lot from this place and indeed it didn’t deliver a a great experience, but at least it is kinda cheap and quantity is big. I ordered a banana murtabak and chicken chikka for a total of 100 HKD and couldn’t finish on the spot so brought a doggy bag home.

Moreover, I think the food is kinda okay, not bad but not great. The samosas I had were very dry, as well as, surprisingly, the curry rice my friend ordered. And they don’t have a lot of sauce to help (why ??) so the experience of eating those meals is a bit disappointing. The chicken tikka was great though.

In conclusion, I dont really recommend this place but can’t advise against totally. I think it’s made for quick and cheap bites and it serves this purpose for sure, but it is not a place to get a great food experience and come back again and again.
Great place to have a quick bite, service is quick
Very delicious food but they don't deliver at all.

result.name: A Kashmir Curry House

reviews.text:
Authentic Indian food in a humble neighborhood, very reasonable price and good food.
Wish I can visit this place more often and sample the entire menu.
Excellent curries and masala, authentic Pakistani cuisine.

This is a good friendly place. The food is good and the prices are reasonable. It is in a working class neighborhood and the decorations are limited. Hygiene is excellent.  Cooks from here are often used temporarily when other restaurants are being started. Selections are limited compared to more expensive places. It is halal and alcohol is not served. There is a wide range of roti available. I have been back many times.
Very good. Not expensive, not cheap. Excellent food.

2018-12-28 1746HKT

up to today, still our (me n wife) favourite for Indian food.

Taste is good, may not be the best, but definitely good value for money.

Place is not big n fancy, but still enjoyable.

result.name: 喀什米爾咖喱屋

reviews.text:
今日咁啱落深水埗,想食咖哩,環境就一般,唔會俾人感覺好污糟坐得唔舒服之類,而且佢哋都好多鄉里專登幫趁.
坐低,望下餐單,食物款式唔多,照舊同去其他同類餐廳一樣,都係點咖哩羊同一杯印度奶茶,ok,啲羊騷味係唔覺嘅,煮得唔太稔,不過入味,咖哩味唔係非常濃嗰種,淡淡哋,不過都好味,同試過嘅其他中東咖哩舖唔同,杯奶茶就無乜茶味,但有一陣蔗糖味,進食期間見到都好多佢哋鄉里過嚟買烤餅(煎餅),同有本地人買外賣,整體覺得食物質素ok.想試下地道嘅中東咖哩,嚟開呢頭可以一試,價錢就因為佢哋無set餐,今餐我一飯($65)一飲品($10),唔算太平亦都唔太貴.
不過下次再有機會應該會先試埋區內另外兩間咖哩屋先會再嚟試其他食品.

Easy to get here and reasonable price for food.
In summer, should try the juicy mango and indian tea. Love to eat different kinds of bread.

深水埗平民化的印度快餐店
地點方便 價錢合宜

Authentic Indian food in a humble neighborhood, very reasonable price and good food.
Wish I can visit this place more often and sample the entire menu.
一句講曬，好抵食好好食！ 食物上枱熱辣辣， 薄餅即叫即整， 印度傳統乳酪飲品比較甜， 不過真係好好味，好好飲！ 幫襯當日大約下晝五點幾，已經有好多人。一半都是印度人幫襯。 實在太美味， 一定會再來！
Excellent curries and masala, authentic Pakistani cuisine.
